AN ACT relating to health care; prohibiting a provider of health
care from providing electroconvulsive therapy to a person
who is less than 18 years of age; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill prohibits a provider of health care from providing, or supervising the
2 provision of, electroconvulsive therapy to a person who is less than 18 years of age
3 regardless of whether the person or his or her parent or legal guardian is willing to
4 authorize the therapy. This bill authorizes the imposition of professional discipline
5 against a provider of health care who violates that prohibition.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 629 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A provider of health care shall not provide, or supervise
4 the provision of, electroconvulsive therapy to a person who is less
5 than 18 years of age regardless of the willingness of the person or
6 his or her parent or legal guardian to authorize such therapy.
7 2. A provider of health care who violates any provision of this
8 section is guilty of unprofessional conduct and is subject to
9 disciplinary action by the board, agency or other entity in this
10 State by which he or she is licensed, certified or registered.
11 3. As used in this section, “electroconvulsive therapy” means
12 the induction of a major motor seizure by applying a brief intense
